As you approach the sunbather, you realize that she's not a sunbather at all, at least not anymore.  It's a mummified corpse, baked in the high California heat until it's as withered as a raisin.
> take sunglasses

> take sunglasses
Should you really, though? Of course, SHE won't care whether you take her sunglasses or not, but... something feels very wrong here.  You wonder if stealing from a corpse is really a very good idea. Then again...
> take sunglasses

> take sunglasses
What the hell... She's not going to miss them.  You pull the sunglasses off of the dead woman's face and stash them in your pocket.  Without her sunglasses, she stares at you with empty sockets.
> wear sunglasses

> wear sunglasses
You slide the sunglasses over your eyes. The world looks a lot darker.
