You are in a plaza.
You can see an acolyte and a statue.
You can go north, east, west, south or southeast.
The boardwalk terminates at a large open plaza.  To the east is the entrance to an aquarium, standing next to a wax museum to the southeast, and a large opulent building, which you recognize as the Paradise Hotel, can be entered to the south.  The boardwalk is to the north. To the west, a pier juts out over the beach and water.

A young man  in a greasy Body Glove T-shirt and baggy swim trunks stands in front of the double doors to the hotel. The hotel's enormous lobby windows have been painted over with heavy matte black paint, but you can vaguely see the outlines of shapes milling about within.
"'Scuse us, coming through!" The three young women you met earlier in the motel parking lot file past you. Valerie stops as she recognizes you.

"You found it!" she beams. "Are you ready? Are you ready to bend your will to the sea?"

You still have no clue what that means.

"I think we understand now," says Valerie seriously, "We weren't sure at first, but then... Cindy found that stash of Marine Snow.  And...it came to use."

She grins widely. Her eyes are glassy and her pupils are fully dialated. Sweat is pouring down her face, though it isn't that hot.

Valerie bounds over to the young man standing in front of the hotel doors.  He leans forward and she whispers something in his ear.  He frowns first, but then smiles a big toothy smile. He steps to one side and pulls open the door. You get the briefest glimpse inside the darkened lobby, seeing nothing but a jumbled pile of overstuffed armchairs turned on their sides.  Squealing with excitement, Valerie hugs her friends before bounding off inside.

Next Ashley walks up to the young man and whispers something into his ear.  He nods and motions her inside, and she disappears through the door after Valerie.  Only Cindy remains.  She comes close and says something to the acolyte that you cannot hear.  His face darkens and he shakes his head.  Cindy is suddenly agitated.  Her eyes wide, she appears to plead with him to reconsider -- though you can't make out what she says from here.  After a few minutes, it's apparent that he's not going to change his mind.  Cindy bursts into tears and runs off, her face in her hands.

The young man closes the door and resumes his position.

