You press the button and you hear the projector behind you flicker to life, projecting an old black and white film reel onto the screen.  It's "Mysteries of the Santa Carcossa Trench," a dull but informative 5 minute kids' film about the fauna of the Santa Carcossa Trench.

The volume is turned up so high that the walls shake and you have to cover your ears.  You hear a sudden clatter outside in the main aquarium, almost as if the vibrating walls have knocked something down.
