You are in a lantern room.
You can see a lighthouse keeper, a lamp, a sphere and a matchbook.
You can go down or northwest.
The metal slat staircase leads to a metal platform in a round glass enclosure. A giant smashed electrical light stands at the room's center. A black obsidian sphere hovers above the broken lamp, suspended in mid-air and emitting a low, almost imperceptible humming.     A body is slouched in the corner, wearing a yellow oil slicker and with a sou'wester pulled down over their face.  One of the windows is smashed; through it, you can access an outside ledge to the northwest.

There is elaborate scrawled writing circling the walls of the room, inlaid into the bare cement above the windows in gold leaf: "I have become Poseidon, Master of the Seas and Tamer of the Waves. All the Waters Recede by My Command."

> search lighthouse keeper

> search lighthouse keeper
Holding your breath, you quickly pat down the pockets of the former lighthouse keeper's slicker.  You find a small glass flask of a strong-smelling alcohol in his breast pocket.
> take flask

> take flask
You pocket the alcohol flask.
> take matchbook

> take matchbook
You pry the matchbook out of the dead lighthouse keeper's hand.
