You are in a ledge.
You can see a nest.
You can go southeast.
You're on a narrow concrete ledge running around the oustide of the lantern house.  The strong wind and dizzying height compell you to hug the wall to avoid following; you'd rather not try to navigate your way around the lip.  The lantern house is accessible via a shattered glass pane to your southwest.

Some shore bird has woven a large mass of tangled seaweed and garbage into a haphazard nest, perched at your feet.
> search nest

> search nest
Wincing at the smell, you reach into the nest and probe your fingers through the soft, rotting kelp.  Your fingers connect with something hard and pull back, finding a small metal key, green with rust, in the palm of your hand.

You hear a sudden groan of a door being opened back inside the lighthouse... Someone has followed you inside...
