You are in a lantern room.
You can see a lighthouse keeper, a lamp and a sphere.
You can go down or northwest.
The metal slat staircase leads to a metal platform in a round glass enclosure. A giant smashed electrical light stands at the room's center. A black obsidian sphere hovers above the broken lamp, suspended in mid-air and emitting a low, almost imperceptible humming.     A body is slouched in the corner, wearing a yellow oil slicker and with a sou'wester pulled down over their face.  One of the windows is smashed; through it, you can access an outside ledge to the northwest.

There is elaborate scrawled writing circling the walls of the room, inlaid into the bare cement above the windows in gold leaf: "I have become Poseidon, Master of the Seas and Tamer of the Waves. All the Waters Recede by My Command."

CLANG...CLANG... CLANG... Something is clumping its way up the metal spiral stairs.  You crane your neck to see and catch a glimpse of the withered corpse in the red bikini.

Your jaw drops and you stumble backwards. The dead woman is very mobile now, stumbling slowly up the stairs with her bony arms outstretched, her vacant eye sockets staring.
> make molotov cocktail

> make molotov cocktail

You strike a match against the match book and stuff it into the flask of alcohol; the high-proof fluid immediately bursts into flames.  Without pausing, you toss the make-shift molotov cocktail at the corpse shambling up the stairs.  It strikes her in the face, shattering and splattering her with flaming liquid.  The corpse stumbles backwards before bursting into flames and tumbling back down the stairs.

In moments, it's completely burned to a crisp and the fire peters out, leaving nothing behind but ash.
