> read notebook

> read notebook
The notebook is mostly illegible scribbles, broken here and there by crude pencil drawings of ocean life.  From what you can make out, the chronicler was mainly interested in keeping a diary of strange fishes that washed up on the Santa Carcossa shoreline.

There are a few legible passages, though:

"EVER SINCE MY ENCOUNTER WITH THE GOBBLER, I HAVE WONDERED WHY. WHY WAS I CHOSEN? WHY DID THE GOBBLER KNOW TO COME TO ME? FOR SO LONG, I WAS SCARED AND ANGRY, LOST IN A WORLD OF DARKNESS. BUT THEN I REALIZED THAT THE GOBBLER HAD KNOWN THE TRUTH OF THE END LONG BEFORE WE EVER DID."

"SOMETHING HAS DRAWN ME BACK TO SANTA CARCOSSA. I BELIEVE THE ANSWER MAY BE HERE. I BELIEVE THAT THE END IS COMING BUT PERHAPS HERE I CAN FIND A WAY TO CONTINUE."

"WORD IS GETTING OUT. MORE SEEKERS COME EVERY DAY. AT FIRST THIS MOTEL WAS PERFECT FOR OUR SMALL GROUP. BUT TOO MANY ARE COMING. WE MUST MOVE. THE OLD PARADISE HOTEL WILL BE PERFECT FOR US."

On the last page, written in tall clear letters, you can read the following statement: "HOW DO YOU BEND YOUR BODY TO THE SEA???? THE ANSWER WAS CLEAR BEFORE MY EYES THE WHOLE TIME, BUT MY SIGHT BLINDED ME. ONLY HE WHO EMBRACES THE SILENT DARKNESS OF THE DEPTHS CAN TRULY UNDERSTAND THE ANSWER:  HOW DO YOU BEND YOUR WILL TO THE SEA? THE FISH CARES NOT FOR THE SHOAL."
