The boardwalk terminates at a large open plaza.  To the east is the entrance to an aquarium, standing next to a wax museum to the southeast, and a large opulent building, which you recognize as the Paradise Hotel, can be entered to the south.  The boardwalk is to the north. To the west, a pier juts out over the beach and water.

A young man  in a greasy Body Glove T-shirt and baggy swim trunks stands in front of the double doors to the hotel. The hotel's enormous lobby windows have been painted over with heavy matte black paint, but you can vaguely see the outlines of shapes milling about within.
> speak to acolyte

> speak to acolyte
"Hello, seeker," says the young man, smiling broadly. "For, if you've come this far and braved this many adversities, I must assume that you are a seeker... You, like so many before you, have arrived at the truth only to find yourself in despair. Am I right?"

You nod. You hold up the Way of the Dolphin paper. "Yes, I found one of these in...Professor Chow's things."

He smiles. "I don't recognize that name," he says, "But I must assume, then, that this Prof. Chow was not prepared to seek. Unlike you,"

You nod.

"Of course, there are many who seek," he continues, "but few who find. The Way of the Dolphin is a journey, a journey away from this dying world to a beautiful new paradise, but only those who are prepared properly can make that journey. Are you ready to begin preparations?"

"Before you can begin preparations, you must show that you are worthy of this journey. You must show that you want to be saved, to be rescued from this dying world. Show me that you will bend to the will of the sea. Only then can you enter the sanctuary and begin preparations as an acolyte of the Way of the Dolphin."

He falls silent. It seems like that's all he has to say.
> speak to acolyte

> speak to acolyte
"Hmm? And how will you bend to the way of the sea?"

You clear your throat and tentatively answer: "The fish cares not for the shoal?"

The acolyte smiles. "You gain wisdom! Your first test has been passed. But are you ready to actually make the leap? Step inside and we'll see!"

He steps aside and gestures for you to enter the hotel.
