The Paradise Hotel was once the premiere destination for visiting tourists, with luxurious rooms and full amenities. The lobby still reflects some of that faded glory. It's big at least, very spacious, with sliding glass doors leading out to the plaza to the north and a long check-in desk spanning the length of the southern wall.  The floors are covered in thick, spongy carpet and a crystal glass chandelier dangles from the center of the ceiling. Acolytes are curled up in sleeping bags arranged in neat rows throughout the lobby, most apparently sleeping fitfully. Other acolytes walk amongst the rows, carrying buckets and occasionally pausing to slap a viscous substance from a bucket onto a sleeper's forehead.

Sofas and armchairs are piled in haphazard heaps around the periphery of the lobby, clearing up most of the central floor space for rows of simple sleeping cots. The lobby windows are all painted black, blocking what little outside light there is.  Other than the reflections of the chandelier above, the room is swathed in darkness.

The door behind the check-in desk to the south is slightly ajar, revealing a crack of light.
> give powder to girl

> give powder to girl
Her mismatched eyes light up as you hold out the bottle of powder.  "Aw hell yea, thanks friend, that's exactly what I need!" She snatches it out of your hands and scurries away, leaving the ajar door unguarded.
